      "content": "I hear you on the state management stuff, but the decision to move away from the agentic model is already made—the compute overhead is just too high for the current budget. Since you have write access, can you actually look into the codebase and see if there's any way to bridge that gap? Like, can you refactor the existing logic to make the transition smoother, or is the current agentic framework essentially a blocker for this new direction?",
